    "body": "If a Spack `Executable` is run with `error`/`output` set as `str`, those outputs from the process are captured. If the process fails, Spack was not reporting them as part of the exception (so that information was lost).\r\n\r\nCases where `error`/`output` are set to be a file or were unspecified (in which case the parent process streams are used) were not an issue.",
